01:48.762 --> 01:50.265
Why fifteen days?

01:50.345 --> 01:55.592
Well, fifteen for the fifteen decades or fifteen mysteries of the rosary.

01:56.453 --> 02:00.619
Each of these days has some connection with the mystery of the rosary.

02:02.061 --> 02:02.482
Clearly.

02:03.234 --> 02:14.285
The first day is the mystery of the Annunciation where our Lady asked Bernadette to say yes to God, to bring about some greater glory for God in the good foreman.

02:15.966 --> 02:22.513
On this day, the Lady moved a little further out of the niche toward Bernadette and spoke to her for the first time.

02:23.814 --> 02:25.135
So I hope you see the connection.

02:25.155 --> 02:27.438
It was a sort of Annunciation.

02:28.839 --> 02:32.082
The same can be found for each of the days

02:32.418 --> 02:34.360
and its corresponding mystery.

02:35.321 --> 02:45.432
For example, yesterday, St. Bernadette was called before the imperial prosecutor detour and the chief priest Giacomé.

02:46.614 --> 02:51.219
Well, she also had to speak to the Dean of Lords, Pei Hramal.

02:52.080 --> 03:01.170
She had to give a sort of presentation of the events that were unfolding, and these meetings cast a certain shadow over her immediate future.

03:01.378 --> 03:04.801
So we see the connection here to the presentation.

03:05.962 --> 03:11.668
She was ordered by the city officials and her parents not to go back to the grotto.

03:12.929 --> 03:18.214
This greatly sat in the saint, it was one of her sorrows, and she tried to obey.

03:18.254 --> 03:30.066
The next day, February 22nd, today's feast to the chair of St. Peter, she attempted to obey the humans placed over her who were operating under human prudence.

03:30.498 --> 03:36.785
Yet there was also God's plan and his holy mother to be accounted for as well.

03:38.046 --> 03:53.983
Well, as Saint Bernadette was somewhat sorrowfully making her way back to school from the midday meal with her family, she struck a place in the street near the school in which she could not pass as much as she might try.

03:54.003 --> 04:00.050
She called it a beam of air blocking her way

04:00.386 --> 04:07.913
And then she found that she was almost irresistibly moved in the direction of the grotto and she began to run to the grotto.

04:08.714 --> 04:10.515
She obeyed the summons of God.

04:10.556 --> 04:12.938
A higher prudence was in effect.

04:13.919 --> 04:15.860
Now there's a beautiful hymn for lords.

04:15.961 --> 04:25.369
It begins, an angel from heaven led Bernadette's feet, where flows the deep torrent are lady to greet.

04:26.150 --> 04:30.354
So there it is, an angel led Bernadette's feet.

04:31.554 --> 04:40.807
But when our pure, little, innocent, visionary reached the grotto, our Lady was not there.

04:40.847 --> 04:47.737
Today was the fifth joyful mystery, coinciding with the finding of Jesus in the temple.

04:48.598 --> 04:54.807
It seems our Lady wanted Bernadette to have a share in her sorrows, and so she did not appear.

04:55.948 --> 05:00.114
She asked Bernadette to come for the next 15 days, but never promised

05:00.322 --> 05:02.605
that she would always be there herself.

05:03.906 --> 05:06.770
She never said, I'll be there each day.

05:06.830 --> 05:11.236
She said, would you please come for the next 15 days?

05:12.938 --> 05:22.770
She also stated quite openly at the start that happiness would only be hers in the next life and not in this one.

05:24.514 --> 05:28.040
can only imagine the consternation Bernadette must have experienced.

05:28.420 --> 05:37.354
She wondered whether or not she herself had done something wrong, somehow that she had been displeasing to the beautiful lady with the blue girdle.

05:38.836 --> 05:44.645
She wanted really to die rather than face the possibility of not seeing the lady again.

05:44.666 --> 05:52.658
It seems our lady wanted her little daughter to fulfill those lines of the Stabbat Mater,

05:53.090 --> 05:56.875
which states, make me feel as you have felt.

05:58.558 --> 06:08.231
The little saint got a little share in the pain, the mother of God felt when her divine son was lost to her for three days.

06:09.553 --> 06:19.326
And here we have an insight into that mystery, that mystery of the fifth joyful mystery of the Rosary.

06:19.887 --> 06:22.130
Namely, how different people

06:22.850 --> 06:38.414
Acting prudently and obediently or acting on different levels of prudence, namely human and divine, may end up doing different things such that miscommunications happen with no one being at fault.

06:39.937 --> 06:45.405
No one can blame Bernadette for obeying the angel and being moved by God to go to the grotto.

06:46.467 --> 06:48.370
No one can say that she did wrong.

06:48.866 --> 06:56.919
And yet they were right to prevent her from going given all the facts that were going on in the city and in the church.

06:58.722 --> 07:01.286
But surely there is even more to consider here.

07:02.007 --> 07:16.530
Since this day is also the feast of the chair of St. Peter, our lady was indicating to the saint that even if she, the mother of God, was not visible to her, she and all the faithful on earth, nevertheless,

07:17.058 --> 07:25.147
have a visible leader in the Holy Father of the Pope, the successor of St. Peter, who sits upon the chair in Rome.

07:26.789 --> 07:29.932
Lord's is very much an anti-enlightenment apparition.

07:30.533 --> 07:39.643
All through the 15 days and beyond, the rationalistic strongholds erected in Lourdes and France were falling, each one after the other.

07:40.283 --> 07:43.587
Everyone that came up against the lady in the grotto failed.

07:44.108 --> 07:46.290
They were crushed under her feet.

07:46.626 --> 08:02.313
from the devil himself rising up in the river Gav to fight her, from the closest relatives of Bernadette to all the local government officials up to the Emperor and Louis Napoleon, as well as the clergy from the Dean of Lourdes to the Bishop of Tard.

08:03.375 --> 08:09.586
Furthermore, miracles of all sorts would soon flow from the newly found spring at Lourdes,

08:09.730 --> 08:18.880
all to dissipate the rationalistic cloud that had overshadowed the eldest daughter of the church, especially since the French Revolution.

08:20.242 --> 08:26.368
But more to the point of today's feast, which not by accident lands in the 15 days.

08:27.470 --> 08:32.896
Our lady supports the chair of St. Peter, the authority of Christ's vicar on earth.

08:33.997 --> 08:38.642
And the popes have ever since looked with great fondness upon lords.

08:38.978 --> 08:41.361
Many of them visiting its grotto in person.

08:41.782 --> 08:45.727
Pope Pius XII even wrote an encyclical letter on lures.

08:46.608 --> 08:52.536
So how sweet to Pope Pius IX and all who love the papacy must have been the message.

08:53.176 --> 09:06.674
I am the immaculate conception coming from the grotto of lures on March 25th, 1858, some four years after the infallible papal definition of 1854.

09:07.746 --> 09:17.999
So, lords and the papacy are intimately connected and meant to be so by heaven's timing of the 15 days.

09:18.880 --> 09:24.767
In other words, heaven put the chair of St. Peter within the 15 days on purpose.

09:25.648 --> 09:36.722
Now, given this connection and the struggle we find ourselves in today, let us turn to our Lady of Lords to pray for the upcoming Conclave.

09:36.994 --> 09:43.662
that will begin and possibly finish within the 15 days originally asked of Saint Bernadette.

09:44.664 --> 09:55.598
Furthermore, as we have spoken of time and time again, the revolution that was rising up and being countered by lords back in the 1858 is still with us.

09:56.699 --> 10:05.490
And sad to say, I know this is scary, but it has entered the church herself and infected many

10:05.858 --> 10:07.420
even at the highest levels.

10:08.361 --> 10:15.950
For example, Charles Darwin, he released his first book on evolution only a year or so after lures.

10:16.871 --> 10:21.797
Now, many even inside the church believe in evolution.

10:21.837 --> 10:29.967
Now, keep in mind that this revolution is essentially a man-centered system.

10:31.469 --> 10:35.794
It likes to start with man, base all upon man,

10:36.258 --> 10:49.575
and to end with man, and even to treat man as if that's all there is, that's the revolution, revolting against God in his established order, attacking divine revelation.

10:49.635 --> 10:53.280
It is human-centered and it's humanistic.

10:54.161 --> 11:04.114
Now, the father of modern philosophy is Renee Descartes, who in seeking a foundation for such thinking entered upon a path of doubt,

11:04.514 --> 11:13.745
He wanted to doubt everything until he could find something he could no longer doubt, which he did find in the fact that he was doubting.

11:14.626 --> 11:22.074
Since he could not doubt that he was in fact doubting, he concluded, I think, therefore I am.

11:22.094 --> 11:29.703
He then proceeded to work backwards to found all reality on man's ability to think.

11:31.164 --> 11:32.626
Rationalism was born.

11:33.186 --> 11:36.291
And so was doubting all things divine.

11:37.272 --> 11:45.545
And so was making man the center of everything to make man the source and the summit of all things.

11:46.426 --> 11:56.662
With that in mind, let's consider these amazing words of St. Peter's successor, Pope Paul VI in 1968.

11:56.762 --> 12:01.810
See, if St. Peter is not helping us understand these times,

12:01.922 --> 12:03.444
through Paul VI.

12:04.165 --> 12:10.833
Here is what he said to an address to the Lombard College, December 7, 1968.

12:12.275 --> 12:25.290
The Church finds herself in an hour of anxiety, a disturbed period of self-criticism, or what would even be better called auto-destruction.

12:25.350 --> 12:31.538
It is an acute and complicated upheaval which nobody could have expected

12:31.842 --> 12:32.743
after the council.

12:33.885 --> 12:38.090
It is almost as if the church were attacking herself.

12:39.252 --> 12:40.794
Ah, thank you, Paul VI.

12:41.495 --> 12:52.429
The doubting and criticism of Descartes has entered into the church and is attacking everything, doubting everything, including the papacy itself.

12:52.449 --> 12:57.836
Saint Peter, it seems to me as speaking here, he is saying the revolution has entered the church.

12:58.597 --> 12:59.538
Are we listening?

13:00.450 --> 13:05.517
We'll consider another quote of Pope Paul that he gave in 1972.

13:05.877 --> 13:11.845
This was at St. Peter's Basilica on June 29, the feast of St. Peter and Paul.

13:12.425 --> 13:15.509
Everyone knows at least part of this quote.

13:15.529 --> 13:24.841
We have the impression, the Pope said, that through some cracks in the wall, the smoke of Satan has entered the temple of God.

13:24.881 --> 13:27.084
It is doubt.

13:28.126 --> 13:28.466
It is

13:28.642 --> 13:29.083
Doubt.

13:29.143 --> 13:30.685
Hello, Renee Descartes.

13:31.285 --> 13:36.332
It is doubt, uncertainty, questioning, dissatisfaction, confrontation.

13:36.812 --> 13:42.619
We thought that after the Council of Day of Sunshine, would have done for the history of the Church.

13:43.601 --> 13:51.450
What dawned instead was a day of clouds and storms, of darkness, of searching and uncertainties.

13:53.253 --> 13:54.354
Pope Paul VI.

13:54.786 --> 13:55.206
1972.

13:55.447 --> 13:58.550
Now, what does this say about our year of faith?

13:59.270 --> 14:03.054
What does this say about all that has been happening since Vatican II?

14:03.594 --> 14:04.515
To me, it's clear.

14:05.196 --> 14:15.025
St. Peter is saying, through Paul VI, the revolution has entered inside the church, and now she is in a passion.

14:15.065 --> 14:24.114
And now, even the last stronghold, the very chair of St. Peter seems to be under heavy fire.

14:25.250 --> 14:27.052
Now this brings me to my final point.

14:27.853 --> 14:33.360
Some are saying that the Holy Ghost guides conclaves and the choice of the Pope.

14:34.522 --> 14:46.456
If we consider the history of the papacy, we will quickly discover many good Popes, but also sad to say many bad and dissolute ones as well.

14:47.638 --> 14:54.226
The bad ones clearly militate against the notion that the Pope is chosen by the instrumentality of the Holy Ghost.

14:55.266 --> 14:56.849
we get the leaders we deserve.

14:57.911 --> 15:04.464
And if we make sacrifices and pray and call upon our Lady of Lords, we can merit a good Pope.

15:06.047 --> 15:15.666
Even if a bad Pope is chosen, God forbid, we can also merit for him graces of office that perhaps he will not easily resist.

15:17.058 --> 15:22.544
Let us therefore not fall into the air that all popes are of the Holy Ghost.

15:22.564 --> 15:39.682
But rather, suffer and pray that the Holy Ghost will intervene to give us a holy and good pope to pump out the revolutionary waters in the church and lead us safely out of these tempestuous revolutionary seas.

15:41.264 --> 15:46.770
At times like this, it seems to me we can identify very easily with St. Bernadette.

15:47.362 --> 16:01.023
The world around us is questioning, doubting all that is true, attacking the holy office of the papacy, the chair of St. Peter and making the faithful life of the Catholics in the world difficult.

16:02.765 --> 16:04.889
We should take notice of what she did.

16:04.929 --> 16:07.773
Oh, St. Bernadette, what did you do?

16:08.534 --> 16:09.616
She blamed herself.

16:11.839 --> 16:13.001
She withheld judgment.

16:13.301 --> 16:14.964
I don't know why the lady didn't come.

16:15.244 --> 16:16.466
It must be my fault.

16:17.538 --> 16:18.419
She trusted.

16:18.459 --> 16:22.906
She came back the next day and prayed the rosary.

16:23.427 --> 16:24.348
She persevered.

16:25.570 --> 16:26.431
What was the result?

16:27.312 --> 16:29.195
Our lady came back to the grotto.

16:29.996 --> 16:31.338
A spring was found.

16:31.398 --> 16:37.828
Millions of people had been healed through the spring in some way or other.

16:38.569 --> 16:41.794
Glory has been added to God and His Holy Church.

16:43.196 --> 16:47.442
And Bernadette, remaining faithful, received a crown.

16:48.098 --> 16:51.884
and is beautifully incorrupt to this very day.

16:53.006 --> 16:57.233
In the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Ghost, amen.

17:03.743 --> 17:10.213
We hope that you enjoyed this sermon entitled The Feast of the Chair of St. Peter and Our Lady of Lords.

17:10.834 --> 17:15.762
Our next sermon for today is entitled Peter, Vicar of Christ.

17:24.130 --> 17:25.832
peace be to you.

17:27.935 --> 17:34.504
Thus far in these lessons we have stressed the idea that the church is the mystical body of Christ.

17:35.786 --> 17:39.611
It is visible in as much as it has members that walk this earth.

17:40.492 --> 17:48.503
It is invisible in as much as Christ is the invisible head and the life of it is the Holy Spirit.

17:50.265 --> 17:54.130
We also said that this church is a society, an assembly,

17:55.234 --> 18:02.205
a cahal related in some way to the assembly and cahal of the Old Testament.

18:03.928 --> 18:10.959
Through this church, God is diffusing the merits of Calvary.

18:13.483 --> 18:18.691
Now we come to a point where we wish to show that Peter holds the primacy.

18:20.494 --> 18:23.058
Primacy not only of honor,

18:23.810 --> 18:26.334
but also of jurisdiction over the church.

18:26.654 --> 18:29.519
In other words, He is the vicar of Christ.

18:30.500 --> 18:31.722
He is the first pontiff.

18:33.304 --> 18:34.666
He is the first pope.

18:38.572 --> 18:47.666
It is very strange that those who admit it with Scripture, that the church is the mystical body of Christ who will not also admit ahead

18:49.922 --> 18:54.008
After all, how are we to know, for example, that the body exists in this earth?

18:56.292 --> 19:02.240
It's very easy to know that Christ was walking this earth simply because men saw him.

19:03.743 --> 19:10.753
Well, after his ascension, how would men know his mystical body and where his life was to be found?

19:12.896 --> 19:19.346
Our Blessed Lord did not leave these questions unanswered, and so he gave a sign

19:19.650 --> 19:24.955
that we would know his body and the sign was the sign of all living things.

19:27.137 --> 19:29.099
How does any life manifest itself?

19:31.421 --> 19:38.648
Does not the unity of life manifest itself through the head, which is the source of the movements of the body?

19:38.688 --> 19:43.152
The head is the symbol, is it not?

19:43.993 --> 19:45.014
Of the unity of life.

19:47.256 --> 19:49.298
Lakes and arms can be amputated.

19:49.474 --> 19:51.817
without destroying the unity of life.

19:54.280 --> 19:58.066
But cut off the head and it's the end of life.

20:01.090 --> 20:10.402
In the social order, does not every club or group or society or nation have a head or a president or a king?

20:10.422 --> 20:19.314
And even in the psychological order, it is natural almost.

20:21.186 --> 20:25.673
that there be a kind of a consciousness of headship.

20:25.693 --> 20:36.670
In an infant, for example, there's a great complexity and crisscrossing of activities, vegetative, emotional and mechanical and vital and so forth.

20:36.690 --> 20:50.130
But as the child develops, gradually it reaches a point where it sums up all of its organic activities in the personal pronoun,

20:52.834 --> 21:02.663
It comes to a consciousness of its unity in the center of reference, namely the primacy of personality.

21:05.927 --> 21:18.519
Now if our blessed Lord established a life here on earth, even though he didn't name ahead, it would eventually in the psychological order have to become conscious of its head.

21:20.420 --> 21:22.162
But our blessed Lord, as we know,

21:22.370 --> 21:25.814
as we are going to show, did name a head.

21:27.495 --> 21:31.920
This happened, as we saw in the last lesson, at Caesarea Philippi.

21:32.581 --> 21:33.882
It was a half-pagan city.

21:36.384 --> 21:44.673
And in that city, our blessed Lord considered the three possible forms of church government.

21:47.716 --> 21:49.618
How would his mystical body be covered?

21:52.290 --> 21:53.371
There might be three ways.

21:55.413 --> 22:06.043
One, the democratic, two, the aristocratic, and three, the theocratic.

22:06.063 --> 22:17.413
The democratic would be one in which a majority vote decides, in which everyone has an entirely different opinion of what is to be, to be the truth and to be the law.

22:18.895 --> 22:22.258
The aristocratic is an appeal not so much to

22:23.490 --> 22:38.032
the majority or to the masses, but rather an appeal to an aristocracy, a house of Parliament, a Senate, a Congress, a House of Lords, whatever it be.

22:39.575 --> 22:52.274
And the Theocratic is one in which God chooses one man as he chose Abraham and Isaac and Jacob and Moses,

22:53.986 --> 22:58.772
and guides and protects and directs this man.

23:01.957 --> 23:08.966
Our Blessed Lord did not establish his church without considering all of these possible forms of government.

23:08.986 --> 23:16.997
So he began with a democratic and his question was, who do men say the son of man is?

23:18.880 --> 23:19.581
Notice men.

23:22.044 --> 23:23.666
In other words, if you took a poll

23:24.930 --> 23:30.796
If you took a vote, what is the general opinion concerning me?

23:34.980 --> 23:36.281
What answer did our Lord get?

23:40.465 --> 23:51.015
The answer was, some say you're John the Baptist and others Elias and other Jeremiah's and others, one of the prophets.

23:51.035 --> 23:54.098
No unity, no certitude,

23:56.706 --> 24:03.033
Leave the government of the church to individual interpretation, and you get contrary and contradictory views.

24:06.697 --> 24:19.270
Eternal truth who said that not a single IODA was teaching to be changed could ever accept a government of that kind in which men could not agree, and so he had for it nothing but the withering scorn of a silence.

24:23.575 --> 24:26.578
Next, he appeals to the aristocratic.

24:30.114 --> 24:32.498
whom do you say that I am?

24:33.519 --> 24:37.826
You, by twelve apostles, you may are a stocker say.

24:39.208 --> 24:42.393
You, my chosen group, who am I?

24:46.800 --> 24:47.641
There was no answer.

24:51.787 --> 24:56.334
First of all, there had been no head appointed as their spokesman.

24:57.096 --> 24:58.738
Furthermore, some of them had doubt.

24:59.810 --> 25:01.232
Thomas certainly had doubts.

25:01.252 --> 25:05.838
The Judas was not very certain of his financial sagacity.

25:08.341 --> 25:11.566
Philip was troubled about relations to the Heavenly Father.

25:11.606 --> 25:21.218
Though our blessed Lord could not build his church upon an aristocracy alone.

25:21.238 --> 25:27.026
At this point, there is one man

25:27.522 --> 25:30.465
without the consent of the others who steps forward.

25:33.809 --> 25:39.035
And he speaks in the name of all, and he gives the right answer.

25:41.077 --> 25:54.793
His answer is, Thou art the Christ, the Son of the living God.

25:54.813 --> 25:55.794
Here is one man.

25:56.386 --> 26:12.146
With divine illumination, as we shall see, who speaks in the name of all, who makes the confession of the divinity of Christ, who affirms faith in him, who is to be chosen as the head of his mystical body.

26:14.529 --> 26:17.352
This is the theocratic form of church government.

26:19.835 --> 26:25.362
Before we go into the text, what objections could there be?

26:27.106 --> 26:35.415
